oc:kn_1d236c59 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before writing any Remotion code for a specific feature area (audio, video, transitions, fonts, etc.)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Load the appropriate domain-specific rule file from rules/ before implementing any Remotion feature. This skill uses progressive disclosure — the SKILL.md is an index, and detailed patterns live in topic-specific rule files." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Each rule file contains critical constraints, API patterns, and code examples specific to its domain that prevent common mistakes and ensure correct usage of Remotion APIs." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_411ba82d a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When embedding any media asset (image, video, audio) in a Remotion composition" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use native HTML <img>, Next.js <Image>, or CSS background-image for images. Always use the <Img> component from 'remotion'. Similarly use <Video> from '@remotion/media' and <Audio> from '@remotion/media'." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Remotion's media components ensure assets are fully loaded before rendering each frame, preventing flickering and blank frames during export." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_67f11970 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When using toneFrequency on <Audio> or <Video> components, or attempting reverse playback" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Pitch shifting (toneFrequency) only works during server-side rendering, not in the Remotion Studio preview or the <Player /> component. Reverse playback is not supported for audio or video." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are platform limitations of Remotion's rendering pipeline. Previewing pitch-shifted audio locally will not reflect the final rendered output, causing user confusion if not documented." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_73edc3b3 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When referencing any local file asset in a Remotion project" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always use staticFile() to reference files from the public/ folder. Never use relative paths or plain string URLs for local assets." ;
    oc:hasRationale "staticFile() returns a properly encoded URL that works correctly when deploying to subdirectories and handles special characters in filenames." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7806583c a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When arranging multiple scenes or elements in a composition timeline" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use <Series> for sequential non-overlapping playback, <Sequence> for delayed/trimmed appearance within a timeline, and <TransitionSeries> from @remotion/transitions for scene transitions with visual effects (fade, slide, wipe). Transitions shorten total duration because scenes overlap during the transition." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Choosing the correct sequencing primitive prevents timing bugs. TransitionSeries overlaps adjacent scenes during transitions, so total duration = sum of sequences minus transition durations, which must be accounted for in composition length." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_97028a42 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When defining composition props and schemas in src/Root.tsx" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use type declarations (not interface) for composition props to ensure defaultProps type safety. All defaultProps values must be JSON-serializable. Use Zod schemas with z.object() at the top level to make compositions parametrizable and editable in the Remotion Studio sidebar." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Type declarations work correctly with the satisfies operator for defaultProps validation. Zod schemas enable visual parameter editing and type-safe dynamic metadata calculation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_df314dec a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing any frame-driven animation or interpolation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "All animations must be driven by the useCurrentFrame() hook. Write timing in seconds and multiply by the fps value from useVideoConfig(). Always use extrapolateRight: 'clamp' and extrapolateLeft: 'clamp' to prevent values from exceeding defined ranges." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Remotion renders each frame independently; useCurrentFrame() provides the deterministic frame index needed for reproducible animations. Unclamped interpolation can produce values outside intended ranges causing visual glitches." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ec60b81f a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any animation in a Remotion composition" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use CSS transitions, CSS animations, or Tailwind animation class names in Remotion components — they will not render correctly during video export." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Remotion renders frames deterministically using React, so CSS-driven animations which depend on real-time browser behavior produce incorrect or inconsistent results." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_f149c353 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When using <Sequence> to schedule when elements appear on the timeline" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always premount any <Sequence> using premountFor to load components in the timeline before they actually play. A good default is premountFor={1 * fps}." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Premounting ensures components (especially those with async data loading or media) are fully initialized before their first visible frame, preventing flash-of-empty-content artifacts." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

